	Forward and Deferred shading differ based on when the lighting is calculated
	
	\begin{itemize}
		\item	Forward calculates the lighting on all fragments, including occluded
		\item	Deferred shading calculates lighting only for non-occluded fragments
	\end{itemize}
	
	Deferred shading can be much faster, by simplifying the lighting calculations but
	
	Forward shading can be more accurate, by knowing edges and transparencies
	
	Additionally, forward shading offers more capabilities and control over lighting
	
